# .worktreeinclude — spec 0.6 (claude-workflow-plugin-e0d.6).
#
# When the worktree-creation machinery (the `--worktree` flag,
# subagent worktrees spawned via `isolation: "worktree"`, and parallel
# sessions in the desktop app) builds a fresh worktree, it copies
# every file matching a pattern here that is ALSO gitignored — tracked
# files are never duplicated. Reference:
#   https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees#copy-gitignored-files-into-worktrees
#
# This file uses `.gitignore` syntax. Comments start with `#`.
#
# Goal: every concurrently spawned specialist boots into a worktree
# that has the same secrets, env, and per-machine settings as the
# parent checkout, so their tests and tooling actually run.

# Environment files (mirrors the .gitignore patterns under "Secrets
# and environment files"). The .env.example IS tracked so it is not
# eligible for copying here — that is correct; we want the developer's
# real .env files copied, not the example.
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.env.local

# Per-developer Claude Code settings. .claude/settings.json is tracked
# (it ships with the plugin); .claude/settings.local.json is the
# user-specific override that holds local-only tweaks. The local file
# is gitignored on most installs (the user's project .gitignore or
# global gitignore), so it needs the explicit copy rule.
.claude/settings.local.json
